load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_CHECK_DECL(symbol, *, define, headers, language) Check if a symbol is declared. This is different from AC_CHECK_SYMBOL - it checks if something is declared (not just #defined). Example: AC_CHECK_DECL("NULL", headers = ["stddef.h"])
AC_CHECK_DECL("stdout", headers = ["stdio.h"]) PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value symbol Name of the symbol to check none define Custom define name (defaults to HAVE_DECL_) None headers Optional list of headers to include None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
10.title: macros.AC_CHECK_DECL

11.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_CHECK_FUNC(function, define, code, file, language) Check for a function. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value function Name of the function (e.g., "printf") none define Custom define name (defaults to HAVE_) None code Custom code to compile (optional) None file Label to a file containing custom code (optional) None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
11.title: macros.AC_CHECK_FUNC

12.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_CHECK_HEADER(header, define, language) Check for a header file. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value header Name of the header file (e.g., "stdio.h") none define Custom define name (defaults to HAVE_) None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
12.title: macros.AC_CHECK_HEADER

13.body:
load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_CHECK_MEMBER(aggregate, member, *, define, headers, language) Check if a struct or union has a member. Example: AC_CHECK_MEMBER("struct stat", "st_rdev", headers = ["sys/stat.h"])
AC_CHECK_MEMBER("struct tm", "tm_zone", headers = ["time.h"]) PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value aggregate Struct or union name (e.g., "struct stat") none member Member name (e.g., "st_rdev") none define Custom define name (defaults to HAVE__) None headers Optional list of headers to include None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
13.title: macros.AC_CHECK_MEMBER

14.body:
load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_CHECK_SIZEOF(type_name, *, define, headers, language) Check the size of a type. WARNING: This macro is NOT cross-compile friendly. It requires compiling and running code to determine the size, which doesn't work when cross-compiling. Example: AC_CHECK_SIZEOF("int") # Sets SIZEOF_INT to the size
AC_CHECK_SIZEOF("size_t", headers = ["stddef.h"]) PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value type_name Name of the type (e.g., "int", "size_t", "void*") none define Custom define name (defaults to SIZEOF_) None headers Optional list of headers to include None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
14.title: macros.AC_CHECK_SIZEOF

15.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_CHECK_SYMBOL(symbol, *, define, code, file, language) Check if a symbol is defined. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value symbol Name of the symbol (e.g., "NULL") none define Custom define name (defaults to HAVE_) None code Custom code that includes necessary headers (optional) None file Label to a file containing custom code (optional) None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
15.title: macros.AC_CHECK_SYMBOL

16.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_CHECK_TYPE(type_name, *, define, code, file, language) Check for a type. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value type_name Name of the type (e.g., "size_t") none define Custom define name (defaults to HAVE_) None code Custom code that includes necessary headers (optional, defaults to standard headers) None file Label to a file containing custom code (optional) None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
16.title: macros.AC_CHECK_TYPE

17.body:
load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_COMPUTE_INT(define, expression, *, headers, language) Compute an integer value at compile time. WARNING: This macro is NOT cross-compile friendly. It requires compiling and running code to compute the value, which doesn't work when cross-compiling. This matches GNU autoconf's AC_COMPUTE_INT signature: AC_COMPUTE_INT([VARIABLE], [EXPRESSION]) This is useful for computing values like sizeof(), alignof(), or other compile-time constants. Example: AC_COMPUTE_INT("SIZEOF_INT", "sizeof(int)")
AC_COMPUTE_INT("MAX_VALUE", "1 << 16")
AC_COMPUTE_INT("TWO", "1 + 1") PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value define Define name for the result (first arg to match autoconf) none expression C expression that evaluates to an integer (second arg) none headers Optional list of headers to include None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
17.title: macros.AC_COMPUTE_INT

18.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_C_BIGENDIAN(define, language) Check byte order (endianness) of the system. WARNING: This macro is NOT cross-compile friendly. It requires compiling and running code to determine endianness, which doesn't work when cross-compiling. Note: The define is set to 1 for big-endian, 0 for little-endian. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value define Define name (defaults to WORDS_BIGENDIAN) "WORDS_BIGENDIAN" language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
18.title: macros.AC_C_BIGENDIAN

19.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_C_INLINE(define, language) Check what inline keyword the compiler supports. Tests inline keyword and defines it to the appropriate value. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value define Define name (defaults to "inline") "inline" language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
19.title: macros.AC_C_INLINE

20.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_C_RESTRICT(define, language) Check if the compiler supports restrict keyword. Note: If restrict is not supported, the define is set to empty string. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value define Define name (defaults to "restrict") "restrict" language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
20.title: macros.AC_C_RESTRICT

21.body:
load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_DEFINE(define, value) Define a configuration macro unconditionally. This is equivalent to GNU Autoconf's AC_DEFINE macro. It creates a define that will always be set in the generated config.h file. Example: AC_DEFINE("CUSTOM_VALUE", "42")
AC_DEFINE("ENABLE_FEATURE", "1")
AC_DEFINE("PROJECT_NAME", '"MyProject"') PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value define Define name (e.g., "CUSTOM_VALUE") none value Value to assign (defaults to "1") "1" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
21.title: macros.AC_DEFINE

22.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_PROG_CC() Check that a C compiler is available. This is mostly a no-op in Bazel since the toolchain must be configured, but returns a check that will verify the compiler works. RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
22.title: macros.AC_PROG_CC

23.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_PROG_CC_C_O(define, language) Check if the compiler supports -c and -o flags simultaneously. Note: If the compiler does NOT support both flags together, the define is set. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value define Define name (defaults to "NO_MINUS_C_MINUS_O") "NO_MINUS_C_MINUS_O" language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
23.title: macros.AC_PROG_CC_C_O

24.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_PROG_CXX() Check that a C++ compiler is available. This is mostly a no-op in Bazel since the toolchain must be configured, but returns a check that will verify the compiler works. RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
24.title: macros.AC_PROG_CXX

25.body: load("@rules_cc_autoconf//autoconf:defs.bzl", "macros") macros.AC_TRY_COMPILE(*, code, file, define, language) Try to compile custom code. Note: This is a rules_cc_autoconf extension. While GNU Autoconf has an obsolete AC_TRY_COMPILE macro (replaced by AC_COMPILE_IFELSE), this version adds support for file-based checks which is useful in Bazel. PARAMETERS Name Description Default Value code Code to compile (optional if file is provided) None file Label to a file containing code to compile (optional if code is provided) None define Define name to set if compilation succeeds None language Language to use for check ("c" or "cpp") "c" RETURNS A JSON-encoded check string for use with the autoconf rule.
25.title: macros.AC_TRY_COMPILE

3.body: Autoconf-like configuration checks for Bazel. This module provides a rule to mimic autoconf functionality, allowing you to generate config.h files by running compilation checks against a cc_toolchain. autoconf module_info
